php-reflint
===========

A linter that finds runtime references which were removed from the official PHP
Syntax in php 5.4 after having been deprecated for a while. We use this for
upgrading our legacy code to new PHP versions.

Based on PHP-Parser by Nikita Popov.

Installation and Usage
----------------------

Install PHP-Parser as documented here:
https://github.com/nikic/PHP-Parser/blob/1.x/doc/1_Installation.markdown

Run

php reflint.php -r /path/to/search/recursively/for/files/ending/in/dotphp

or

php reflint.php list.php of.php paths/to/single.php files.php

For more help, try

php reflint.php --help
